<div id="review_1745168191" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1745168191" />
    <a title="Lorraine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12034546-lorraine"><img alt="Lorraine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609874355p2/12034546.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1745168191?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lorraine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lorraine" href="/user/show/12034546-lorraine">Lorraine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1745168191" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6022659129466065557">Every year, for 9 years now, I dip into &quot;For Colored Girls Who Have Considered Suicide When The Rainbow Is Enough&quot;, Ntozake Shange (10th time). This choreopoem has a very special place in my heart. First heard of it after I&apos;d watched Tyler Perry&apos;s movie of the same title, released 2010, and immediately bought the DVD, searched for the book for months, and bought it too.<br/><br/>When I first got the book, I read it cover to cover, then now and again I&apos;d reread my favourite poems with the corresponding mov</span>
  <span id="freeText6022659129466065557" style="display:none">Every year, for 9 years now, I dip into "For Colored Girls Who Have Considered Suicide When The Rainbow Is Enough", Ntozake Shange (10th time). This choreopoem has a very special place in my heart. First heard of it after I'd watched Tyler Perry's movie of the same title, released 2010, and immediately bought the DVD, searched for the book for months, and bought it too.<br /><br />When I first got the book, I read it cover to cover, then now and again I'd reread my favourite poems with the corresponding movie scenes not far from my mind.<br /><br />A powerful book to have within easy reach as it is a strong reminder that change starts with us. We have the power to stop generational curses. We have the power to move away from toxic situations.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6022659129466065557" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


