<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer18283459834511749684">Ntozake Shange (pronounced En-toe-ZAHK-kay SHONG-gay) was an African-American playwright, performance artist, and writer who is best known for her Obie Award winning play <i>for colored girls who have considered suicide/when the rainbow is enuf</i>.<br/><br/>Among her honors and awards are fellowships from the Guggenheim Foundation and the Lila Wallace-Reader&apos;s Digest Fund, and a Pushcart Prize. </span>
  <span id="freeText18283459834511749684" style="display:none">Ntozake Shange (pronounced En-toe-ZAHK-kay SHONG-gay) was an African-American playwright, performance artist, and writer who is best known for her Obie Award winning play <i>for colored girls who have considered suicide/when the rainbow is enuf</i>.<br /><br />Among her honors and awards are fellowships from the Guggenheim Foundation and the Lila Wallace-Reader's Digest Fund, and a Pushcart Prize. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18283459834511749684" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

